<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Damage Shield 101</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Nyxx">Nyxx</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:39 p.m. 22/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Damage Shield 101<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/povar.cgi?read=50" TARGET=_self>O'Keils Radiation Spell</A> (Lemaitre)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>First off, the smartest move is to target the tank of your group just moments prior to battle when you cast O'keil's Radiation (can you tell i got C's in English?). This does two things that us Wizzes love: 1.) the shield "burns" the critter when it hits the tank. This increases the "hate" list of the monster to the fighter and not onto our easily-bruised bodies. 2.) If your tank is worth his/her salt, than he/she will be Taunting like mad to get all the monsters to attack him/her (lousy in English and Political Correctness. Why do I even try?) Ultimately this wears down multiple creatures so when the time comes to check each monster into the Smack Down Hotel, they will have been beaten up a bit and primed for extinction. Hope this helps.

<BR>Nyxx.
<P>&gt; Does anyone know how this spell works. It
<BR>&gt; says it's a Damage shield. However, when I
<BR>&gt; cast it, I don't get an affect icon showing
<BR>&gt; it on me. I also never see npc's taking
<BR>&gt; damage. It uses considerable mana and time
<BR>&gt; (for my level) and I don't see any use, as
<BR>&gt; of yet, for it. Someone with some insight,
<BR>&gt; please fill me in.
<P>&gt; Regards,
<BR>&gt; The Erudite Wizard, Lemaitre
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
